{"title_page": "Samuel Zauber", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Samuel Zauber\n| image               =\n| fullname            =\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|1901|01|09|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Timi\u0219oara]], [[Austria\u2013Hungary]]\n| death_date         = {{Death date and age|1986|06|10|1900|11|10|df=yes}}\n| death_place         =\n| height              =\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 1924\u20131925\n| clubs1 = [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps1 =\n| goals1 =\n| years2 = 1925\u20131926\n| clubs2 = [[FC Sportul Studen\u021besc Bucure\u0219ti|Sportul Bucure\u0219ti]]\n| caps2 =\n| goals2 =\n| years3 = 1928\u20131936\n| clubs3 = [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps3 =\n| goals3 =\n| nationalyears1 = 1931\n| nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Samuel Zauber''' (9 January 1901 [[Timi\u0219oara|Temesv\u00e1r]] \u2013 10 June 1986 [[Jerusalem]]) was a [[Romania]]n [[association football]] player who was on the [[Romanian national football team]] for the first ever [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]. Since 1964 he lived in [[Jerusalem]], in [[Israel]].\n\n== Playing career ==\n\n=== Club ===\nZauber played his club football for [[History of the Jews in Romania|Jewish]] side, [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]].\n\n=== International ===\nZauber was the back up goalkeeper for Romania at the 1930 FIFA World Cup in [[Uruguay]]. Afterwards, he represented Romania in the [[Balkan Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Anii 1931 - 1935|url=http://www.info.frf.ro/index.php?articol=196|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120210221914/http://www.info.frf.ro/index.php?articol=196|publisher=Romanian Football Federation|trans-title=Years 1931 - 1935|language=Romanian|archivedate=10 February 2012|accessdate=2009-06-28|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;Maccabi Bucure\u015fti\n*[[Liga II]] (1): [[1934\u201335 Divizia B|1934\u201335]]\n\n===International===\n;Romania\n*[[Balkan Cup]] (1): [[Balkans Cup 1929-31|1929\u201331]]\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*28/5/1992 \u05db\"\u05d4 \u05d0\u05d9\u05d9\u05e8 \u05ea\u05e9\u05e0\"\u05d1 Reshumot Yalkut hapirsumim nr.4008 death date in Israel official monitor\n\n== External links ==\n*{{RomanianSoccer|2269/samuel-zauber.htm}}\n*{{NFT|36721}}\n\n{{Romania Squad 1930 World Cup}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zauber, Samuel}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1986 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Timi\u0219oara]]\n[[Category:Romanian Jews]]\n[[Category:Jewish footballers]]\n[[Category:Jewish Romanian sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:1930 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Liga II players]]\n[[Category:FC Sportul Studen\u021besc Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Maccabiah Games competitors for Romania]]\n[[Category:Maccabiah Games footballers]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n\n\n{{Romania-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Samuel Zauber\n| image               =\n| fullname            =\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|1901|01|09|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Timi\u0219oara]], [[Austria\u2013Hungary]]\n| death_date         = {{Death date and age|1986|06|10|1900|11|10|df=yes}}\n| death_place         =\n| height              =\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 1924\u20131925\n| clubs1 = [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps1 =\n| goals1 =\n| years2 = 1925\u20131926\n| clubs2 = [[FC Sportul Studen\u021besc Bucure\u0219ti|Sportul Bucure\u0219ti]]\n| caps2 =\n| goals2 =\n| years3 = 1928\u20131936\n| clubs3 = [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps3 =\n| goals3 =\n| nationalyears1 = 1931\n| nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Samuel Zauber''' (9 January 1901 [[Timi\u015foara|Temesv\u00e1r]] \u2013 10 June 1986 [[Jerusalem]]) was a [[Romania]]n [[association football]] player who was on the [[Romanian national football team]] for the first ever [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]. Since 1964 he lived in [[Jerusalem]], in [[Israel]].\n\n== Playing career ==\n\n=== Club ===\nZauber played his club football for [[History of the Jews in Romania|Jewish]] side, [[Maccabi Bucure\u015fti]].\n\n=== International ===\nZauber was the back up goalkeeper for Romania at the 1930 FIFA World Cup in [[Uruguay]]. Afterwards, he represented Romania in the [[Balkan Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Anii 1931 - 1935|url=http://www.info.frf.ro/index.php?articol=196|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120210221914/http://www.info.frf.ro/index.php?articol=196|publisher=Romanian Football Federation|trans-title=Years 1931 - 1935|language=Romanian|archivedate=10 February 2012|accessdate=2009-06-28|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;Maccabi Bucure\u015fti\n*[[Liga II]] (1): [[1934\u201335 Divizia B|1934\u201335]]\n\n===International===\n;Romania\n*[[Balkan Cup]] (1): [[Balkans Cup 1929-31|1929\u201331]]\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*28/5/1992 \u05db\"\u05d4 \u05d0\u05d9\u05d9\u05e8 \u05ea\u05e9\u05e0\"\u05d1 Reshumot Yalkut hapirsumim nr.4008 death date in Israel official monitor\n\n== External links ==\n*{{RomanianSoccer|2269/samuel-zauber.htm}}\n*{{NFT|36721}}\n\n{{Romania Squad 1930 World Cup}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zauber, Samuel}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1986 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Timi\u0219oara]]\n[[Category:Romanian Jews]]\n[[Category:Jewish footballers]]\n[[Category:Jewish Romanian sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:1930 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Liga II players]]\n[[Category:FC Sportul Studen\u021besc Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Maccabiah Games competitors for Romania]]\n[[Category:Maccabiah Games footballers]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Bucure\u0219ti players]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n\n\n{{Romania-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wbm1058", "label": "safe", "comment": "Timi\u0219oara(viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samuel_Zauber"}
{"title_page": "Bihar State Road Transport Corporation", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox Public transit\n | box_width       =\n | name            = Bihar State Road Transport Corporation worst bus company ever <br> \u092c\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0930 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u092f \u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0917 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0935\u0939\u0928 \u0928\u093f\u0917\u092e\n | image           = BSRTC_logo.png\n | imagesize       = 300 px\n | owner           = [[Government of Bihar]]\n | locale          = [[Bihar]], [[Jharkhand]]\n | transit_type    = Intercity bus service within [[Bihar|State of Bihar]] and selected cities neighbouring states <br> Local bus service in selected cities<ref>[http://www.gauravluxury.com/pgaboutus.aspx about us] Gaurav Luxury.</ref>\n | lines           =\n | stations        =\n | ridership       = \n | chief_executive = Sanjay Kumar Aggarwal, IAS <ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Monthly-pass-system-for-city-buses-soon/articleshow/53216142.cms | title=Monthly pass system for city buses soon | publisher=The Times of India | date=14 July 2016 | accessdate=16 September 2016}}</ref> '''(Administrator)'''\n | headquarters    = [[Bailey Road, Patna]]\n | website         = http://bsrtc.org.in/\n | began_operation = 1953 as Rajya Transport<br>1959 as Bihar State Road Transport Corporation\n | ended_operation =\n | operator        = \n | marks           =\n | vehicles        = \n | train_length    =\n | headway         =\n | map             =\n | map_name        =\n | map_state       = \n}}\n\n'''Bihar State Road Transport Corporation''' or BSRTC is a state-owned worst ever road transportation company in Bihar with compared to other Indian state.<ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/luxury-bus-service-between-bihar-and-jharkhand-from-dec-12/886286/ \"Luxury bus service between Bihar and Jharkhand from Dec 12\"] ''The Indian Express''. Retrieved 10 December 2011</ref> BSRTC was set up in 1959 under the provisions of Road Transport Corporation Act, 1950. It is wholly owned by the [[Government of Bihar]].\n\n==History==\nPrior to May 1959, road transport services  in [[Bihar]] were managed by Rajya Transport, which was set up in the year 1953 with the nationalisation of some routes in the state. Rajya Transport and Communication, [[Government of Bihar]] and was departmentally administered till it was transferred in May 1959 to Bihar State Road Transport Corporation (BSRTC), a statutory corporation created under the provisions of the State Road Transport Corporation Act, 1950.\n\nTotal capital invested in BSRTC till March 1983 was {{INR}}53.9 crores out of which {{INR}}24.77 crores was the share capital of the state government and {{INR}}465 crores loans from the same source, while {{INR}}24.48 crores was contributed from other sources in the shape of shares and loans. Investment in BSRTC was second largest investment made by the [[Bihar Government]], after [[Bihar State Electricity Board]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=mJu80WQlIGgC&pg=PA457&lpg=PA457&dq=bihar+State+Road+Transport+Corporation+founded&source=bl&ots=Aq-86fLYuT&sig=77ZsXyO2iXLtBPGytH4RDSXzwh0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=dws4Utq8KoyJrAe5mYH4Cw&ved=0CEoQ6AEwBjgK#v=onepage&q=bihar%20State%20Road%20Transport%20Corporation%20founded&f=false Productivity and Management of State Level Public Enterprises, Part 2] google book</ref>\n[[File:BSRTC Mercedes buses.png|thumb|BSRTC Mercedes buses]]\nCurrently the Administrator of Bihar State Road Transport Corporation is Shri Amrendra Prasad Singh,IAS.\n\n==Patna City Bus Service==\nThis service is started on 3 May 2018 by BSRTC that was inaugurated by Hon'ble Chief Minister of Bihar Shri Nitish Kumar from Gyan Bhawan, Gandhi Maidan at two routes i.e Gandhi Maidan to Danapur (111) and the second one is from Gandhi Maidan to Danapur Railway Station (111A). Later on, Bihar State Road Transport Corporation had started city bus service on various routes of Patna and nearby. Almost 50 thousands passenger travels through city bus services across all routes. But as per the demands of the daily passengers it needs to bring new buses on all routes to enhance the quality and safety of the passengers.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\nBSRTC recently started the service of luxury volvo buses from Patna and Kishanganj to Gajiyabad.\n\n==External links==\n*[http://transport.bih.nic.in/ Official website of Transport Deptt., Govt. of Bihar]\n\n{{State agencies of Bihar}}\n{{State owned road transport companies in India}}\n\n[[Category:State agencies of Bihar]]\n[[Category:Transport in Bihar]]\n[[Category:Bus companies of India]]\n[[Category:State road transport corporations of India]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Patna]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox Public transit\n | box_width       =\n | name            = Bihar State Road Transport Corporation<br> \u092c\u093f\u0939\u093e\u0930 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u092f \u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0917 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u0935\u0939\u0928 \u0928\u093f\u0917\u092e\n | image           = BSRTC_logo.png\n | imagesize       = 300 px\n | owner           = [[Government of Bihar]]\n | locale          = [[Bihar]], [[Jharkhand]]\n | transit_type    = Intercity bus service within [[Bihar|State of Bihar]] and selected cities neighbouring states <br> Local bus service in selected cities<ref>[http://www.gauravluxury.com/pgaboutus.aspx about us] Gaurav Luxury.</ref>\n | lines           =\n | stations        =\n | ridership       = \n | chief_executive = Sanjay Kumar Aggarwal, IAS <ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Monthly-pass-system-for-city-buses-soon/articleshow/53216142.cms | title=Monthly pass system for city buses soon | publisher=The Times of India | date=14 July 2016 | accessdate=16 September 2016}}</ref> '''(Administrator)'''\n | headquarters    = [[Bailey Road, Patna]]\n | website         = http://bsrtc.org.in/\n | began_operation = 1953 as Rajya Transport<br>1959 as Bihar State Road Transport Corporation\n | ended_operation =\n | operator        = \n | marks           =\n | vehicles        = \n | train_length    =\n | headway         =\n | map             =\n | map_name        =\n | map_state       = \n}}\n\n'''Bihar State Road Transport Corporation''' or BSRTC is a state-owned worst ever road transportation company in Bihar with compared to other Indian state.<ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/luxury-bus-service-between-bihar-and-jharkhand-from-dec-12/886286/ \"Luxury bus service between Bihar and Jharkhand from Dec 12\"] ''The Indian Express''. Retrieved 10 December 2011</ref> BSRTC was set up in 1959 under the provisions of Road Transport Corporation Act, 1950. It is wholly owned by the [[Government of Bihar]].\n\n==History==\nPrior to May 1959, road transport services  in [[Bihar]] were managed by Rajya Transport, which was set up in the year 1953 with the nationalisation of some routes in the state. Rajya Transport and Communication, [[Government of Bihar]] and was departmentally administered till it was transferred in May 1959 to Bihar State Road Transport Corporation (BSRTC), a statutory corporation created under the provisions of the State Road Transport Corporation Act, 1950.\n\nTotal capital invested in BSRTC till March 1983 was {{INR}}53.9 crores out of which {{INR}}24.77 crores was the share capital of the state government and {{INR}}465 crores loans from the same source, while {{INR}}24.48 crores was contributed from other sources in the shape of shares and loans. Investment in BSRTC was second largest investment made by the [[Bihar Government]], after [[Bihar State Electricity Board]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=mJu80WQlIGgC&pg=PA457&lpg=PA457&dq=bihar+State+Road+Transport+Corporation+founded&source=bl&ots=Aq-86fLYuT&sig=77ZsXyO2iXLtBPGytH4RDSXzwh0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=dws4Utq8KoyJ